noun.description: Something which springs out or issues forth. Also in extended use: a result or outcome.

verb.description: To spring out or issue forth. Also figurative. Now chiefly literary and poetic.
To spring out of; to spring beyond or further than. Now rare.

origin: Mid 16th century. From out- + spring, after outspring or to spring out<br>Middle English; earliest use found in Peri Didaxeon. From out- + spring. Compare to spring out.
